    const ParamPoint2& param_point
) {
    // Similar approach with temporary metric tensor
    ...
}
```

This approach:
1. Makes it explicit these are pure functions depending only on their inputs
2. Removes the redundancy of having both member variables and parameters
3. Keeps the metric tensor's role in the conversion process clear
4. Maintains all the validation and conversion logic in one place

